---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Colophon · ${site.name}`}
  description="How kj5irq.radio is built: Astro, two fonts, one accent color, no tracking."
>
  <article class="prose colophon">
    <header>
      <p class="label">Colophon</p>
      <h1>How this site is built</h1>
    </header>

    <p>
      Static pages built with <a href="https://astro.build" rel="noopener">Astro</a>, written in
      Markdown, hosted on GitHub Pages behind Cloudflare DNS. The source is public in
      <a href="https://github.com/KJ5IRQ/kj5irq.radio" rel="noopener">the repo</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Type is Source Serif 4 for words and IBM Plex Mono for data, both self-hosted. The site is
      currently wearing its World Cup 2026 kit: saltire navy, gold, and a tartan ribbon that still
      carries a stripe of the usual Ford Field Green. The everyday colors return after the final.
    </p>
    <p>
      No analytics, no cookies, no third-party scripts, no tracking of any kind. The only
      JavaScript on the site is the theme toggle.
    </p>
    <p>
      Statuses and dates on project pages are real and maintained by hand. If something says
      active, it is running; if it says archived, it retired honestly.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .colophon header {
    padding-block: var(--space-8) var(--space-2);
  }

  .colophon {
    padding-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }
</style>
